1
00:01:37,967 --> 00:01:42,263
"Random thoughts
for Valentine's Day, 2004.

2
00:01:44,014 --> 00:01:47,226
"Today is a holiday invented
by greeting-card companies

3
00:01:48,060 --> 00:01:50,437
"to make people
feel like crap.

4
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:56,068
"I ditched work today.

5
00:01:58,404 --> 00:02:00,739
"Took a train out to Montauk.

6
00:02:02,825 --> 00:02:04,535
"I don't know why.

7
00:02:06,287 --> 00:02:08,497
"I'm not an impulsive person.

8
00:02:16,130 --> 00:02:19,216
"I guess I just woke up
in a funk this morning.

9
00:02:19,717 --> 00:02:21,510
"I gotta get my car fixed."

10
00:02:22,178 --> 00:02:24,388
Hi, Cindy. It's Joel.

11
00:02:26,932 --> 00:02:29,477
Listen, I don't feel
very well today.

12
00:02:30,561 --> 00:02:32,396
No, food poisoning,
I think.

13
00:02:33,189 --> 00:02:35,774
"It's goddamn freezing
on this beach.

14
00:02:36,192 --> 00:02:38,777
"Montauk in February.
Brilliant, Joel.

15
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:44,492
"Pages ripped out.
Don't remember doing that.

16
00:02:47,703 --> 00:02:50,748
"It appears this is
my first entry in two years.

17
00:02:59,965 --> 00:03:01,675
"Sand is overrated.

18
00:03:02,885 --> 00:03:05,054
"It's just tiny little rocks.

19
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:17,191
"If only I could
meet someone new.

20
00:03:18,317 --> 00:03:20,194
"I guess my chances
of that happening

21
00:03:20,229 --> 00:03:21,786
"are somewhat diminished,

22
00:03:21,821 --> 00:03:25,574
"since I'm incapable
of making eye contact
with a woman I don't know.

23
00:03:26,951 --> 00:03:31,205
"Maybe I should
get back together with Naomi.
She was nice.

24
00:03:32,331 --> 00:03:33,833
"Nice is good.

25
00:03:35,793 --> 00:03:37,294
"She loved me.

26
00:04:14,582 --> 00:04:17,543
"Why do I fall in love
with every woman I see

27
00:04:17,578 --> 00:04:20,504
"who shows me
the least bit of attention?"

28
00:05:02,171 --> 00:05:03,172
Hi.

29
00:05:03,923 --> 00:05:06,008
I'm sorry?
I just said hi.

30
00:05:06,801 --> 00:05:08,177
Hi, hello.

31
00:05:09,553 --> 00:05:11,347
Okay if I sit closer?

32
00:05:14,099 --> 00:05:15,684
How far are you going?

33
00:05:16,227 --> 00:05:17,874
Rockville Center.

34
00:05:17,909 --> 00:05:19,522
Get out. Me, too.

35
00:05:20,022 --> 00:05:21,030
Really?

36
00:05:21,065 --> 00:05:22,066
What are the odds?

37
00:05:24,902 --> 00:05:26,737
Listen, do I know you?

38
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:31,992
Do you ever shop
at Barnes and Noble?

39
00:05:32,027 --> 00:05:33,209
Sure.

40
00:05:33,244 --> 00:05:34,849
That's it!
Yeah?

41
00:05:34,884 --> 00:05:36,455
I've seen you, man.

42
00:05:37,081 --> 00:05:40,793
Book slave there
for five years now.

43
00:05:41,377 --> 00:05:42,468
Jesus!

44
00:05:42,503 --> 00:05:44,588
I would have thought
I would remember you.

45
00:05:44,623 --> 00:05:46,507
It might be the hair.

46
00:05:46,542 --> 00:05:47,556
What might?

47
00:05:47,591 --> 00:05:49,426
It changes a lot,
the color.

48
00:05:49,677 --> 00:05:51,929
That's why you might
not recognize me.

49
00:05:52,096 --> 00:05:54,160
It's called Blue Ruin.
Right.

50
00:05:54,195 --> 00:05:56,225
The color.
Snappy name, huh?

51
00:05:56,260 --> 00:05:57,434
I like it.

52
00:06:00,729 --> 00:06:04,400
This company makes
a whole line of colors
with equally snappy names.

53
00:06:04,435 --> 00:06:07,987
You've got Red Menace,
Yellow Fever,
Green Revolution.

54
00:06:09,113 --> 00:06:11,761
That would be a job,
coming up with those names.

55
00:06:11,796 --> 00:06:14,980
You think there could
possibly be a job like that?

56
00:06:15,015 --> 00:06:18,164
I mean, how many hair colors
could there be? 15 maybe?

57
00:06:18,581 --> 00:06:20,541
Someone's got that job.

58
00:06:21,542 --> 00:06:24,170
Agent Orange.
I came up with that one.

59
00:06:25,337 --> 00:06:27,756
I apply my personality
in a paste.

60
00:06:28,257 --> 00:06:30,050
I doubt that very much.

61
00:06:31,177 --> 00:06:35,222
Well, you don't know me,
so you don't know, do you?

62
00:06:38,767 --> 00:06:42,396
I'm sorry.
I was just trying to be nice.

63
00:06:44,106 --> 00:06:45,900
Yeah. I got it.

64
00:07:05,628 --> 00:07:07,505
My name's Clementine,
by the way.

65
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:08,672
I'm Joel.

66
00:07:09,173 --> 00:07:10,424
Hi, Joel.

67
00:07:11,801 --> 00:07:13,559
No jokes about my name.

68
00:07:13,594 --> 00:07:15,846
Oh, no.
You wouldn't do that.

69
00:07:15,881 --> 00:07:17,556
You're trying to be nice.

70
00:07:18,182 --> 00:07:20,684
I don't know any jokes
about your name.

71
00:07:20,719 --> 00:07:22,353
Huckleberry Hound.

72
00:07:23,938 --> 00:07:25,863
I don't know
what that means.

73
00:07:25,898 --> 00:07:28,567
Huckleberry Hound?
What are you, nuts?

74
00:07:28,734 --> 00:07:30,486
It's been suggested.

75
00:07:30,736 --> 00:07:34,198
O£, my darling, o£, my darling
O£, my darling Clementine

76
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:39,036
You are lost and gone forever
Dreadful sorry, Clementine

77
00:07:39,578 --> 00:07:40,628
No?

78
00:07:40,663 --> 00:07:42,039
I'm sorry.

79
00:07:42,832 --> 00:07:45,042
It's a pretty name, though.
It really is nice.

80
00:07:45,077 --> 00:07:49,004
It means merciful, right?
Clemency?

81
00:07:49,839 --> 00:07:51,514
Although it hardly fits.

82
00:07:51,549 --> 00:07:53,926
I'm a vindictive little bitch,
truth be told.

83
00:07:53,961 --> 00:07:56,018
I wouldn't think that
about you.

84
00:07:56,053 --> 00:07:58,264
Why wouldn't you think that
about me?

85
00:07:58,848 --> 00:08:00,349
I don't know.

86
00:08:04,353 --> 00:08:05,938
You seem nice.

87
00:08:06,397 --> 00:08:07,982
Now I'm nice?

88
00:08:08,607 --> 00:08:11,401
Oh, God, don't you know
any other adjectives?

89
00:08:11,436 --> 00:08:14,196
I don't need nice.
I don't need myself to be it

90
00:08:14,231 --> 00:08:16,157
and I don't need anybody
to be it at me.

91
00:08:16,192 --> 00:08:17,283
Okay.

92
00:08:23,456 --> 00:08:24,790
It's Joel, right?

93
00:08:26,083 --> 00:08:27,168
Yes.

94
00:08:28,711 --> 00:08:30,504
I'm sorry I yelled at you.

95
00:08:31,255 --> 00:08:33,632
I'm a little
out of sorts today.

96
00:08:43,476 --> 00:08:45,192
My embarrassing admission

97
00:08:45,227 --> 00:08:47,771
is I really like
that you're nice right now.

98
00:08:49,565 --> 00:08:53,402
I can't tell
from one moment to the next
what I'm going to like,

99
00:08:53,437 --> 00:08:56,906
but right now
I'm glad you are.

100
00:09:05,581 --> 00:09:08,584
I have some stuff
that I probably should...

101
00:09:11,253 --> 00:09:13,923
I'm writing...
I'm sorry. Okay.

102
00:09:13,958 --> 00:09:15,591
No.
Sure. That's okay.

103
00:09:18,719 --> 00:09:20,638
Take care, then.

104
00:09:20,673 --> 00:09:21,722
Jesus.

105
00:09:37,404 --> 00:09:40,199
I could give you a ride
if you need.

106
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,284
It's cold.

107
00:09:42,952 --> 00:09:45,204
Yeah! Okay. It is frosty.

108
00:09:45,913 --> 00:09:47,922
You're not a stalker
or anything, right?

109
00:09:47,957 --> 00:09:50,835
I'm not a stalker.
You're the one
that talked to me, remember?

110
00:09:50,870 --> 00:09:53,129
That is the oldest trick
in the stalker book.

111
00:09:53,164 --> 00:09:55,589
Really?
There's a stalker book?

112
00:09:58,467 --> 00:10:00,219
I've got to read that one.

113
00:10:05,307 --> 00:10:08,102
Look, I'm sorry
if I came off sort of nutso.

114
00:10:08,686 --> 00:10:10,027
I'm not really.

115
00:10:10,062 --> 00:10:13,232
That's okay.
I didn't think you were.

116
00:10:19,613 --> 00:10:21,782
Do you want
to have a drink?

117
00:10:22,032 --> 00:10:24,452
I have lots of drinks,
and I could...

118
00:10:27,121 --> 00:10:30,666
Never mind.
Sorry, that was stupid.
I'm embarrassed now.

119
00:10:30,701 --> 00:10:32,293
Good night, Joel.

120
00:10:52,188 --> 00:10:53,814
Two Blue Ruins.

121
00:10:56,108 --> 00:10:57,158
Thank you.

122
00:10:57,193 --> 00:10:58,486
Drink up, young man.

123
00:10:59,528 --> 00:11:02,490
It'll make
the whole seduction part
less repugnant.

124
00:11:06,202 --> 00:11:08,579
I'm just kidding!
Come on.

125
00:11:15,336 --> 00:11:17,713
You're kind of close-mouthed,
aren't you?

126
00:11:17,748 --> 00:11:18,839
I'm sorry.

127
00:11:20,633 --> 00:11:23,427
You know, my life isn't
that interesting.

128
00:11:24,887 --> 00:11:27,306
I go to work, I come home.

129
00:11:28,557 --> 00:11:30,559
I don't know what to say.

130
00:11:31,435 --> 00:11:33,395
You should read my journal.

131
00:11:34,104 --> 00:11:37,233
I mean, it's just blank.

132
00:11:37,775 --> 00:11:40,993
Really? Does that
make you sad or anxious?

133
00:11:41,028 --> 00:11:44,573
I'm always anxious,
thinking I'm not living
my life to the fullest.

134
00:11:44,608 --> 00:11:46,540
Taking advantage
of every possibility

135
00:11:46,575 --> 00:11:50,371
and making sure
I'm not wasting one second
of the little time I have.

136
00:11:50,406 --> 00:11:52,623
I think about that.
Yeah?

137
00:11:57,378 --> 00:11:59,171
You're really nice.

138
00:11:59,964 --> 00:12:02,383
God, I have to stop
saying that.

139
00:12:04,552 --> 00:12:07,138
I'm gonna marry you.
I know it.

140
00:12:09,932 --> 00:12:11,058
Okay.

141
00:12:16,063 --> 00:12:20,067
Joel, you should
come up to the Charles
with me sometime.

142
00:12:20,609 --> 00:12:22,528
It gets frozen
this time of year.

143
00:12:22,563 --> 00:12:24,530
That sounds scary.
Exactly.

144
00:12:25,531 --> 00:12:28,451
I'll pack a picnic,
a night picnic.

145
00:12:29,034 --> 00:12:30,953
Night picnics are different.

146
00:12:32,705 --> 00:12:34,373
That sounds good.

147
00:12:35,458 --> 00:12:37,543
But I should go now.

148
00:12:38,961 --> 00:12:40,316
You should stay.

149
00:12:40,351 --> 00:12:41,672
No, I really have...

150
00:12:42,715 --> 00:12:44,508
I have to get up
so early and...

151
00:12:44,543 --> 00:12:46,673
I would like you
to call me.

152
00:12:46,708 --> 00:12:48,804
Would you do that?
I'd like it.

153
00:12:48,839 --> 00:12:49,805
Yes.

154
00:12:54,310 --> 00:12:57,354
Wish me
a happy Valentine's Day
when you call.

155
00:12:57,730 --> 00:12:59,106
That'd be nice.

156
00:13:40,231 --> 00:13:42,149
What took you so long?

157
00:13:42,184 --> 00:13:43,734
I just walked in.

158
00:13:45,236 --> 00:13:46,654
You miss me?

159
00:13:48,030 --> 00:13:49,532
Oddly enough, I do.

160
00:13:50,825 --> 00:13:53,744
You said "I do."
I guess that means
we're married.

161
00:13:53,953 --> 00:13:55,329
I guess so.

162
00:13:55,955 --> 00:13:58,457
Tomorrow night?
Honeymoon on ice?

163
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:01,001
It's really solid
this time of year.

164
00:14:02,002 --> 00:14:04,588
I don't know.
Come on.

165
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:14,265
It's so beautiful.

166
00:14:15,683 --> 00:14:16,934
Isn't it?

167
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:22,690
Don't go too far.

168
00:14:25,359 --> 00:14:26,819
Are you okay?

169
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,575
Oh, my ass!

170
00:14:34,994 --> 00:14:37,580
I think I should go back.
Come on!

171
00:14:37,615 --> 00:14:39,130
But what if it breaks?

172
00:14:39,165 --> 00:14:41,542
"What if?"
Do you really care
right now?

173
00:14:42,418 --> 00:14:44,044
Come here, please.

174
00:14:51,927 --> 00:14:54,305
Slidey-slidey.

175
00:14:54,763 --> 00:14:56,390
This looks good.

176
00:14:56,974 --> 00:14:58,434
Let me show you
this one thing.

177
00:14:58,469 --> 00:15:00,269
What are you doing?

178
00:15:02,897 --> 00:15:04,064
Come on.

179
00:15:09,570 --> 00:15:11,447
Think I heard a crack.

180
00:15:11,947 --> 00:15:15,117
It's not going to crack.
Or break.

181
00:15:15,152 --> 00:15:16,577
It's so thick.

182
00:15:19,121 --> 00:15:21,874
Show me
which constellations
you know.

183
00:15:24,627 --> 00:15:26,504
I don't know any.

184
00:15:28,380 --> 00:15:30,466
Show me which ones
you know.

185
00:15:30,501 --> 00:15:31,467
Okay.

186
00:15:37,807 --> 00:15:39,183
There's Osidius.

187
00:15:39,475 --> 00:15:40,476
Where?

188
00:15:41,435 --> 00:15:43,062
Right there. See?

189
00:15:43,437 --> 00:15:45,648
A sort of a swoop
and a cross.

190
00:15:46,315 --> 00:15:48,150
Osidius the Emphatic.

191
00:15:50,110 --> 00:15:51,945
You're full of shit, right?

192
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:53,781
No. Osidius, right there.

193
00:15:54,323 --> 00:15:56,075
Swoop and a cross.

194
00:15:56,110 --> 00:15:57,827
Shut the fuck up!

195
00:16:12,466 --> 00:16:14,093
Cock-a-doodle-doo.

196
00:16:18,889 --> 00:16:21,725
Sorry to wake you,
but we're here.

197
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,696
Can I come over
to your house,

198
00:16:34,864 --> 00:16:38,033
to sleep? I'm so tired.

199
00:16:39,785 --> 00:16:42,371
Okay. Yeah, sure.

200
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,874
Let me get my toothbrush.

201
00:17:07,688 --> 00:17:08,772
Yes?

202
00:17:09,523 --> 00:17:11,066
Can I help you?

203
00:17:11,650 --> 00:17:13,235
What do you mean?

204
00:17:14,069 --> 00:17:16,322
Can I help you
with something?

205
00:17:17,281 --> 00:17:18,365
No.

206
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:21,250
What are you doing here?

207
00:17:21,285 --> 00:17:23,996
I'm not really sure
what you're asking me.

208
00:17:27,041 --> 00:17:28,209
Thanks.

209
00:19:16,650 --> 00:19:18,451
