210
00:19:18,486 --> 00:19:19,785
What number is that?

211
00:19:19,820 --> 00:19:21,245
I don't know
what number that is.

212
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:23,824
Jesus Christ.
You'd think they'd
light the number

213
00:19:23,859 --> 00:19:25,242
or at least put
a number on...

214
00:19:25,277 --> 00:19:26,660
Is that him?
I think so.

215
00:19:26,695 --> 00:19:28,287
Yeah, that's him.

216
00:19:28,788 --> 00:19:30,164
That's him.

217
00:19:45,012 --> 00:19:47,014
Hey, Joel.
Frank.

218
00:19:50,893 --> 00:19:52,061
Shit.

219
00:19:52,728 --> 00:19:56,607
Jesus. The only
Valentine's Day cards I get
are from my mother.

220
00:19:56,642 --> 00:19:58,567
How pathetic is that?

221
00:19:58,984 --> 00:20:02,196
You're lucky
you have Clementine.
She is way cool.

222
00:20:02,571 --> 00:20:05,199
You got any
big Valentine's Day plans
with her?

223
00:20:09,161 --> 00:20:10,336
No.

224
00:20:10,371 --> 00:20:13,582
It's only a day away.
Better make some
reservations or something.

225
00:20:13,617 --> 00:20:15,876
Don't want to end up
at Mickey D's, right?

226
00:20:15,911 --> 00:20:17,211
McRomance!

227
00:20:17,378 --> 00:20:19,943
You want some fries
with that shake?

228
00:20:19,978 --> 00:20:22,508
I have to go to sleep now,
Frank.

229
00:20:23,425 --> 00:20:24,510
It's 8:30.

230
00:20:53,247 --> 00:20:54,915
Patrick, stop it.

231
00:21:13,601 --> 00:21:15,478
Okay.

232
00:21:22,485 --> 00:21:24,403
Showtime at the Apollo.

233
00:21:36,665 --> 00:21:37,833
Quiet.

234
00:21:47,343 --> 00:21:48,969
Get it off your head.

235
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,474
Hey, Joel.
What's up?

236
00:21:54,934 --> 00:21:56,268
Hi, Frank.

237
00:22:01,857 --> 00:22:06,153
I only get Valentine's Day
cards from my mom.
How pathetic is that?

238
00:22:07,696 --> 00:22:10,199
You're lucky
you have Clementine, Joel.

239
00:22:10,491 --> 00:22:13,869
You got any
big Valentine's Day plans
with her?

240
00:22:15,162 --> 00:22:16,205
No.

241
00:22:16,664 --> 00:22:20,167
It's only a day away.
Better make
a reservation somewhere.

242
00:22:20,835 --> 00:22:23,129
Don't want to end up
at Mickey D's.

243
00:22:24,171 --> 00:22:25,888
Oh, no.
Yes.

244
00:22:25,923 --> 00:22:29,385
Valentine's Day
is three days away.
I want it resolved.

245
00:22:29,718 --> 00:22:31,685
I'm willing to be the one
to resolve it.

246
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:34,723
So I call her,
and she's changed
her number.

247
00:22:35,099 --> 00:22:38,359
So I walked over
to Antic Attic
to get her something.

248
00:22:38,394 --> 00:22:42,022
I thought I'd go over to work,
give her an early Valentine.

249
00:22:43,983 --> 00:22:45,860
And you won't believe it.

250
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:49,572
She's there with this guy,

251
00:22:50,239 --> 00:22:52,116
this really young guy.

252
00:22:52,575 --> 00:22:56,036
And she looks at me like
she doesn't even know
who I am.

253
00:22:56,704 --> 00:22:57,746
Excuse me?

254
00:22:58,747 --> 00:23:00,332
Can I help you
find something, sir?

255
00:23:04,336 --> 00:23:05,880
Hey, Clem-ato.

256
00:23:06,714 --> 00:23:09,758
Patrick! Baby boy!

257
00:23:13,137 --> 00:23:14,638
